1
00:00:01,420 --> 00:00:02,350
Two weeks ago,

2
00:00:02,460 --> 00:00:05,260
an invisible dome crashed
down on Chester's Mill,

3
00:00:05,430 --> 00:00:07,340
cutting us off from the rest of the world.

4
00:00:07,420 --> 00:00:10,089
Why the dome is here
or what mysteries lie ahead,

5
00:00:10,090 --> 00:00:11,180
we still don't know.

6
00:00:11,310 --> 00:00:13,809
Every day it tests our limits,

7
00:00:13,810 --> 00:00:16,710
bringing out the best
and the worst in us.

8
00:00:18,160 --> 00:00:20,360
Some say we'll be stuck here forever,

9
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:24,360
but we will never stop
fighting to find a way out.

10
00:00:25,370 --> 00:00:29,269
Chester's Mill sentences
Dale Barbara to death.

11
00:00:29,270 --> 00:00:31,500
The egg... it's doing something.

12
00:00:31,710 --> 00:00:33,949
This has to be the way
the dome picks a new leader.

13
00:00:33,950 --> 00:00:35,400
She's your monarch.

14
00:00:36,190 --> 00:00:39,880
Big Jim, you're a sick bastard.

15
00:00:40,210 --> 00:00:42,119
The butterfly makes some kind of spot.

16
00:00:42,120 --> 00:00:43,859
Why is it getting dark
in the middle of the day?

17
00:00:43,860 --> 00:00:45,659
My wife, Pauline, before she passed,

18
00:00:45,660 --> 00:00:47,729
she kept saying one thing
over and over, like a mantra:

19
00:00:47,730 --> 00:00:48,829
"The pink stars are falling."

20
00:00:48,830 --> 00:00:50,219
Our whole town is as good as dead

21
00:00:50,220 --> 00:00:51,959
if we let this fallinto the wrong hands.

22
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:54,340
How do we protect
Chester's Mill and save Barbie?

23
00:00:54,350 --> 00:00:55,346
We can't.

24
00:00:56,040 --> 00:00:57,539
Dad, what's happening?

25
00:00:57,540 --> 00:00:59,093
Now, son, do it now!

26
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:00,467
Now, Junior!

27
00:01:01,227 --> 00:01:11,405
<i>Corrections & Re-Sync
A&D - internationals subs
www.facebook.com/AD.ItalianSubtitles</i>

28
00:01:47,660 --> 00:01:48,660
Dad?

29
00:01:49,600 --> 00:01:50,950
What's happening?

30
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,520
What's that sound?

31
00:01:56,360 --> 00:01:57,855
Pull the lever, son.

32
00:02:00,490 --> 00:02:01,650
Do it, Junior!

33
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:04,191
- Do it now!
- I'm afraid.

34
00:02:29,660 --> 00:02:31,260
What the hell is that?

35
00:02:31,610 --> 00:02:32,610
Look!

36
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:45,169
Look out! Move!

37
00:02:51,790 --> 00:02:53,490
Linda, what's happening?

38
00:02:53,630 --> 00:02:54,919
They're unconscious

39
00:02:54,920 --> 00:02:56,415
but still breathing.

40
00:02:57,730 --> 00:02:59,080
Jim, let me help.

41
00:03:00,070 --> 00:03:00,999
What, set you free?

42
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,739
There are people out there,
your people, that need help.

43
00:03:03,740 --> 00:03:05,640
Nice try, Barbie. Do it, son.

44
00:03:05,650 --> 00:03:08,100
No, Junior, Junior, look out there.

45
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:09,909
The sound is making people sick.

46
00:03:09,910 --> 00:03:11,360
We need to stop it.

47
00:03:14,060 --> 00:03:15,260
I can't do it.

48
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:16,239
What are you doing?

49
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:18,199
I think the dome's trying
to tell us something.

50
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:19,380
That's nonsense.

51
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:20,379
We should go there.

52
00:03:20,380 --> 00:03:21,949
It could have answers for what's happening.

53
00:03:21,950 --> 00:03:23,000
The dome doesn't have answers.

54
00:03:23,010 --> 00:03:24,568
Yes, it does, Dad.

55
00:03:25,100 --> 00:03:27,500
The dome is more than you think it is.

56
00:03:27,740 --> 00:03:29,290
It's shown me things.

57
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:32,400
If you're too scared to do it,
I'll do it. Look out.

58
00:03:32,430 --> 00:03:33,430
Stop.

59
00:03:36,220 --> 00:03:37,230
What are you doing, Linda?

60
00:03:37,330 --> 00:03:38,886
I'm being reasonable.

61
00:03:39,660 --> 00:03:42,760
After what I've seen,
I think maybe Junior's right.

62
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:45,470
We'd need to take a trip to the dome

63
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:48,500
before we do something
we're all going to regret.

64
00:03:56,212 --> 00:03:58,124
Come on.

65
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:03,700
Come on.

66
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,030
What happened?

67
00:04:07,190 --> 00:04:09,890
I don't know.
She was drowning in the lake.

68
00:04:10,820 --> 00:04:11,880
She just appeared.

69
00:04:12,030 --> 00:04:13,572
I have no idea where she came from.

70
00:04:19,890 --> 00:04:21,240
Here, let me try.

71
00:04:31,420 --> 00:04:32,369
It's a good thing you were here.

72
00:04:32,370 --> 00:04:34,420
I saw strange lights
coming out of the lake.

73
00:04:34,710 --> 00:04:37,080
We got to get her and you dry.
Can you walk?

74
00:04:37,110 --> 00:04:38,579
Uh, if it's not too far.

75
00:04:38,580 --> 00:04:40,480
It's just through the woods.

76
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,164
What the hell?!

77
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,400
It's magnetic.

78
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:03,050
What's happening?

79
00:05:04,340 --> 00:05:05,840
- Linda..
- Barbie!

80
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,280
My cuffs!

81
00:05:12,140 --> 00:05:13,580
Hold on! I got you!

82
00:05:16,910 --> 00:05:17,910
Help me!

83
00:05:20,450 --> 00:05:21,400
Help!

84
00:05:22,710 --> 00:05:24,139
- Hurry!
- I can't.

85
00:05:24,140 --> 00:05:25,990
- Junior!
- Help me! Help!

86
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,450
- Okay.
- Come on.

87
00:05:32,230 --> 00:05:33,110
Linda!

88
00:05:33,350 --> 00:05:34,370
Linda, get out of here.

89
00:05:34,390 --> 00:05:35,359
- Get out of here!
- Barbie, I can't.

90
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,129
I almost got it, hold on.

91
00:05:36,130 --> 00:05:38,370
- Linda!
- Get out of the way, Linda!

92
00:05:38,670 --> 00:05:40,040
Almost... almost...

93
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:42,030
Get out of the way!

94
00:05:42,830 --> 00:05:44,810
Linda, run! Run!

95
00:05:45,430 --> 00:05:46,240
Go!

96
00:05:56,481 --> 00:06:05,490
Corrections & Re-Sync
A&D - internationals subs
